      "message": "I think you must issue an error message if it's not 1 or 0 because if the user enters something else you do not know what the intention of the user is. I do not think it is safe to assume \"do not blacklist\" if the data entered is other than 1.\n\nA person could have put in \"11\" as a typo and thinks they have put in a valid blacklist entry but they will not have done so.",
